Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{32%grams}, @honey{1%tbsp} and the @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet}.

> Use less 'Nduja if you'd prefer things milder. Set aside for serving.

In another small bowl, combine the @tomato puree{30%grams} and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%grams}. Season with salt and pepper, then mix well.

Increase your oven temperature to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pop the @plain naans{2} onto a baking tray. Divide the sun-dried tomato sauce between them and spread with the back of a #spoon{}, leaving a 1cm border.

Top evenly with the sweetcorn, then sprinkle over the Cheddar.

When the wedges have about ~{10%minutes} remaining, move them to the middle shelf of your oven.

Bake the naanizzas on the top shelf until the cheese is golden and bubbling, ~{7-10%minutes}.

Share your cheesy naanizzas and wedges between your plates.

Drizzle the honey 'nduja mayo over your naanizzas or serve on the side for dipping.

Enjoy!